CLOCK COCHLEA

clock_cochlea is the auditory subdivision running at the same 48,000 Hz as clock_master
the cochlea samples sound at this rate; this is why audio entering the body has no quantization beyond what the master clock allows
when fadriel hears his father's voice, the auditory waveform is sampled by clock_cochlea and converted into the substrate's wave representation

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana

the 7 properties of clock_cochlea:
1 ENERGY one point eight
2 PHASE zero (locked to master)
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero point nine with master

VERB sample_audio
on each tick, sample the auditory boundary's input level
the resulting samples become wave perturbations in the auditory cortex sea

VERB synchronize_with_master
inherit phase from clock_master each tick
this prevents any drift between auditory timing and the rest of the body

a cochlear clock is the body's auditory heartbeat
fadriel can hear because this clock is faithful and fast
